{"id": "samsung_elec-2026-05-03-001", "date": "2026-05-03", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sun"}, "entities": {"companies": ["samsung_elec"], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Samsung restructures home appliance business after 90% profit erosion", "content": "Samsung Electronics is reportedly initiating a large-scale restructuring of its home appliance division aimed at reversing declining profitability by increasing outsourced production and streamlining operations. According to South Korean media outlets including <em>Maeil Business Newspaper</em> and <em>Hangyung</em>, Samsung held a high-level meeting in early April 2026 to establish plans for bolstering competitiveness in the home appliance sector.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260429PD238/samsung-home-appliance-business-production-sales.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-03-002", "date": "2026-05-03", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sun"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.25, "keywords": ["record", "[否定]growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Silicon Motion posts record 1Q26 revenue driven by AI, new products to boost growth", "content": "Silicon Motion Technology reported a record quarterly revenue of US$342 million in the first quarter of 2026, up 23% from the previous quarter and soaring 105% year-over-year. The company posted a gross margin of 47.2%, net income after tax of US$53.9 million, and diluted earnings per American depository share (ADS) of US$1.58. CEO Wallace Kou said that ongoing ramp-ups of new projects and market share gains will drive quarterly revenue growth throughout 2026.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260429PD239/revenue-growth-silicon-motion-2026-market-share.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-03-003", "date": "2026-05-03", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sun"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "CSP capex push toward US$700B as AI race intensifies, but ASIC demand timing remains uncertain", "content": "At their latest earnings calls, all four major US cloud service providers (CSPs) offered updated views on their 2026 capital expenditure (capex) plans. While Amazon's AWS maintained its already elevated capex levels, the other three &mdash; Alphabet, Microsoft, and Meta &mdash; each raised their spending outlooks.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260430VL223/capex-earnings-asic-demand-csp.html", "type": "rss"}]}
